{{Infobox organization | name = Decarcerate PA | logo = File:Decarcerate PA logo.png | image = | image_border = | size = <!-- default 400px --> | alt = | caption = | abbreviation = DPA | motto = No New Prisons, Decarceration, Community Reinvestment | formation = 2011 | type = | purpose = [[Criminal Justice]], [[Activism]], [[Community Organizing]], [[Prison Reform]] | location = [[Pennsylvania]] | key_people = | affiliations = | num_volunteers = | website = [http://decarceratepa.info] }}
'''Decarcerate PA''' is a [[grassroots]], all-volunteer coalition seeking to challenge mass [[incarceration]] in [[Pennsylvania]]. Decarcerate PA's platform (No New Prisons, Decarceration, Community Reinvestment) has been endorsed by almost 100 organizations.<ref>{{cite web|author=Mar 29 2014 - 9:00am |url=http://decarceratepa.info/decarcerate-pa-platform |title=Decarcerate PA Platform &#124; Decarcerate PA |publisher=Decarceratepa.info |date= |accessdate=2014-03-25}}</ref> Decarcerate PA is an intentionally democratic organization that follows a [[ACT UP#Structure of ACT UP|committee structure]], with each committee dedicated to separate tasks. Since 2011, the coalition has been challenging the construction of two new prisons outside of [[Philadelphia]] in [[Montgomery County, Pennsylvania]] at the site of [[State Correctional Institution - Graterford]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://citypaper.net/article.php?Documents-raise-questions-about-cost-of-new-prison-18059 |title=Documents raise questions about cost of new prison |work=[[Philadelphia City Paper]] |date= |accessdate=2014-03-25 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140208083117/http://citypaper.net/article.php?Documents-raise-questions-about-cost-of-new-prison-18059 |archivedate=2014-02-08 |df= }}</ref> In 2013, Decarcerate PA organized a 113-mile march from [[Philadelphia]] to [[Harrisburg, Pennsylvania]], the state capital, to protest Pennsylvania Governor [[Tom Corbett]] and the [[Pennsylvania]] legislature's decision to increase prison funding and decrease funding in [[public education]] and social services.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://citypaper.net/article.php?March-to-Harrisburg-demands-budget-for-people-not-prisons-17898 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20140325162848/http://citypaper.net/article.php?March-to-Harrisburg-demands-budget-for-people-not-prisons-17898 |dead-url=yes |archive-date=2014-03-25 |title=March to Harrisburg demands budget for people not prisons |work=Philadelphia City Paper |date= |accessdate=2014-03-25 }}</ref>
