{{Infobox person | name = Luc Nkulula | image = LucNkulula.png | image_size = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = October 18, 1985 | birth_place = | death_date = June 10, 2018 | death_place = [[Goma]], [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]] | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = | residence = | nationality = | other_names = | known_for = | education = | alma mater = | employer = | occupation = Political activist | title = | salary = | networth = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | party = | boards = | children = | spouse = | parents = | relatives = }} '''Luc Nkulula''' (October 18, 1985 - June 10, 2018) was a Congolese political activist. ==Biography== He joined [[Lutte pour le changement|LUCHA]] in 2012, and he became one of its leading members.<ref name="guardianobit">{{cite news |last1=Maclean |first1=Ruth |title=Luc Nkulula obituary |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/jul/18/luc-nkulula-obituary |accessdate=July 27, 2018 |work=The Guardian |date=July 18, 2018}}</ref> He met President [[Joseph Kabila]] and asked him to step down in 2016.<ref name="guardianobit"/> His activism involved encouraging young people in his country to be involved in public affairs and pick up [[litter]].<ref name="guardianobit"/>
Nkuluka died on the night of June 9-10, 2018 as his house burnt down.<ref name="hrwcongolese">{{cite web |last1=Sawyer |first1=Ida |title=Congolese Democracy Activist’s Death Mourned |url=https://www.hrw.org/news/2018/06/11/congolese-democracy-activists-death-mourned |website=[[Human Rights Watch]]|date=June 11, 2018}}</ref> The death was deemed "suspicious" by other LUCHA members<ref name="rfiobit">{{cite news |title=Mort de Luc Nkulula en RDC: ouverture d’une enquête judiciaire |url=http://www.rfi.fr/afrique/20180611-rdc-mort-luc-nkulula-lucha-incendie-maison |accessdate=July 27, 2018 |work=Radio France Internationale |date=June 11, 2018}}</ref>, even if "an investigation blamed a faulty solar panel"<ref>[https://www.bbc.com/news/av/world-africa-46101253/the-congolese-protester-who-was-arrested-beaten-and-became-a-martyr ''The Congolese protester who was arrested, beaten and became a martyr'', BBC news, 5 November 2018].</ref>.
